<body>

    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Finding Leads OOP with Strong Hands when your Opponent Lacks Bluffs</h1>
        </header>
        <main>
            <article>
                <h2>Consider Leading the River When</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Villain has a non-polarized range that is SD heavy and significantly lacks air combos AND</li>
                    <li>Your hand is worth more than a check AND</li>
                    <li>Your range can support betting</li>
                </ul>
                <p>SRP BvB: 2c3c4c xc 6d xc 6c CAN LEAD</p>
                <p>SRP MPvsBB: 8c6c9s D33 R50 C 3h B70 C 4c LEAD ALL IN </p>
                <p>4B BTNvsBB: Jd5h2c B20 C 3d B25 C 5s CANT LEAD</p>
                <p>Do <b>NOT</b> use this play when opponent has a polar turn range containing many <b>non-SD bluffs</b>
                    that will shove river when we check.</p>


            </article>
        </main>
    </div>

</body>

